# 2. いざ、ショッピングへ

Saki: Kanade! This shop carries lots of different types of outerwear!
Kanade: Wow, you're right... I don't even know where to begin...
Saki: They seem to be sorted based on category. This looks like the corner for basic coats, and those are all casual jackets...
Saki: Oh, look at this boa fleece! It's so fluffy and adorable!!
Kanade: (I was a little worried that she wouldn't get to have much fun helping me shop...)
Saki: Oh, it's even reversible! And both colors are really cute!
Kanade: (But I guess my worries were misplaced.)
Saki: Wait, I shouldn't be the one having all the fun. I almost forgot that we're here to find you a new jacket, Kanade...!
Saki: Did you have any particular styles or traits in mind?
Kanade: So, above all else, it needs to be warm... But not too heavy, if possible.
Kanade: What else...? It'd be nice if it were made of a material that's easy to maintain. Also, a simple design would be preferable.
Saki: I see. In other words, it needs to be comfortable and easy to keep clean!
Saki: In that case, we might want to try going over to the outdoor goods shop...
Kanade: The outdoor goods?
Saki: Yes! Recently, all the big outdoor brands have been making really cute clothes that you can wear day to day!
Kanade: I had no idea. Then, why don't we go take a look?
Kanade: Umm... Would you mind showing me the way?
Saki: Of course♪ It's right this way!
Saki: Here we are! What do you think?
Kanade: Oh, these come in simple designs... I could wear these like normal.
Saki: Hehe. See what I mean? All that's left is to find something that's both warm and light...
Saki: Oh, what about this down jacket? It's fluffy but not heavy, and seems really warm!
Kanade: Yes, you're right. It shouldn't be all that taxing to wear this.
Saki: Oh, these overcoats also seem pretty versatile!
Saki: You can block the wind and stay warm by popping the collar... Hey, it even says that you can throw it in a washing machine!
Kanade: Oh, you don't have to send it to the dry cleaners...?
Saki: Pretty incredible, right?!
Saki: I know. If you're interested in any of these, then why don't you try them on? We can try asking the staff.
Kanade: Okay, let's do that. Umm... Excuse me...
Clerk: Thank you!
Kanade: Phew...
Saki: I'm glad you were able to find a jacket you like!
Kanade: I really appreciate it, Tenma. There's no telling how long that would've taken if I were by myself. Honestly, I might've gotten exhausted and picked something just to be done...
Saki: Hehe♪ It's nice to know that you should be able to have a warm and cozy winter now♪
Kanade: Yes, you've been a tremendous help. Which is why I'd like to repay the favor somehow...
Saki: No, you don't have to do that! I wanted to help you!
Saki: Plus, while looking around with you, I ended up finding a really cute scarf♪
Kanade: But...
Saki: Not only that, I had a really fun time today thanks to you, Kanade!
Kanade: Huh?
Saki: Because you're able to pull off whatever you wear! I really enjoyed watching you try on different clothes!
Saki: So, there's no need to pay me back!
Kanade: Okay, if you're sure...
Saki: I'm sure! Oh, but...
Saki: If possible...
Saki: I would like to chat with you some more, Kanade.
Kanade: With me...?
Saki: Yes! Ichi and Hona have already told me so much about you.
Saki: I've been hoping that we'd get a chance to sit down and chat!
Kanade: I can't guarantee that we're going to strike up a good conversation. So, as long as you're okay with that...
Saki: You mean it?
Saki: Oh, but I have work after this...! Can we meet again sometime soon?!
Kanade: Sure.
Saki: Thank you so much! Then, we should probably swap our contact info!
Kanade: Umm... I forget how to actually do that on this device...
Saki: You tap here, hit this mark and... Oh, there we go!
Kanade: Yes, I can add you as a friend now...
Saki: All done! Hehe. Thank you again so much!
Saki: Anyway, I'll message you later! We can go to a cafe or something!
Kanade: Okay. Have fun at work.
Kanade: (I really can't thank Tenma enough...)
Kanade: (I don't know if chatting with me will make up for what she did today...)
Kanade: But I am sort of looking forward to talking to her again...
Mizuki: <Alright, thanks for waiting. I'm back.>
Kanade: <Oh, Amia, welcome back...>
Ena: <What were you doing just now?>
Mizuki: <I went to grab a blanket. And a toasty drink while I was at it♪>
Ena: <Yeah, it has been freezing lately. It's hard to work at night without those things...>
Mafuyu: <Really?>
Ena: <Wait, aren't you cold? I mean, if I don't turn the heater on, I can't draw because my hand becomes completely frozen!>
Mizuki: <Yeah, I guess artists do have it pretty rough this time of year. But speaking of how cold it's been...>
Mizuki: <You said you were gonna buy a new jacket, K. Did you already get one?>
Kanade: <Oh, yes... I managed to get one.>
Kanade: <What's more, while I was walking over to the mall today...>
Mizuki: <Really?! And Saki helped you pick it out?!>
Kanade: <Yes, she helped me find a good one after asking me about my preferences. I really can't thank her enough...>
Ena: <I mean, I'm just as surprised that you went out to buy new clothes yourself, K...>
Ena: <Still, a jacket from an outdoor goods shop... I wouldn't have thought of that, but it probably does suit you really well.>
Mizuki: <Especially since they make stuff with cute designs now♪ I might go over sometime to try and dig up a few hidden gems.>
Kanade: (Hm? My phone says I have a message. But from who...?)
Kanade: <Oh...>
Message from Saki: <Thank you again for today, Kanade! I had a lot of fun shopping with you♪>
Message from Saki: <If possible, would you like to go to a cafe with Ichi and me sometime?>
Kanade: (It's from Tenma... And she's already inviting me to meet with her again.)
Mafuyu: <Is something wrong, K...?>
Kanade: <Oh, I received a message from Tenma...>
Kanade: <She asked if I'd like to go to a cafe with her and Hoshino.>
Mizuki: <Hey, that's great♪ Saki's really nice, so I'm sure you two will hit it off!>
Ena: <She even went out of her way to make sure Ichika would be there. That's pretty sharp of her.>
Kanade: <Sharp...?>
Mafuyu: <You'll have an easier time talking to her if someone you both know is also there, no...?>
Kanade: <Oh, right...>
Kanade: <Then, before I forget, I'll reply to her.>
Mizuki: <Oh, what are you gonna say?>
Kanade: <“Thank you very much for inviting me”...?>
Ena: <I'd go with something a little more casual.>
Kanade: <More casual...>
Kanade: <Then... “Sounds good”?>
Mafuyu: <That should work...>
Kanade: <It's sent...>
Kanade: (Now I'm really looking forward to talking to her again...)
